{"word":"παρθενεύω","slug":"παρθενεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παρθενεύω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>σω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:παρθένος'><el>παρθένος</el></a>\n<p/><i>to bring up as a maid</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to lead a maiden life, remain a maid</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>πολιὰ</el> (<a href='S:neuter'>neut.</a> <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>) <el>παρθενεύεται</el> <i>grows</i> gray <i>in maidenhood</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/>"}]}